column1: Sample # - this is the number of the sample collected in a trap during the time period covered in column C
column2: Box # - this is the number on the box in which these vials of insects are contained
column3: Date - this is the time period during which invertebrates were trapped for this sample
column4: ID - this is the location in the box for this vial, row A, column 1
column5: Location - this is the location where the sample was collected (NHMU: Natural History Museum of Utah; Marr Lib: Marriot Library at the University of Utah)
column6: Roof/Ground - this is where the traps were located at each location (Ground: at ground level; roof: on the green roof)
column7: Combi/Pitfall - this is the type of trap used to collect the sample (Combi: combination trap that catches aerial invertebrate; Pitfall: pitfall trap that catches ground crawling invertebrates)
column8: Order - this is the taxonomic order of the collected invertebrates)
column9: Family - this is the taxonomic family of the invertebrates collected
column10: Pollinator - this is whether or not the invertebrate is a known pollinator (Yes) or not (No)
column11: Amount - this is the number of each invertebrate of this morphospecies in the sample
